A 28-year-old suspect has been arrested for possession of
dagga worth R500 000. The vehicle travelling from the Eastern Cape was bust by the
George Serious Organized Crime Investigation members assisted by the Public
Order Policing. Lieutenant Colonel Philani Nkwalase said they received
information about a vehicle that was travelling from the Eastern Cape to George
transporting dagga. ALSO READ: EASTERN CAPE HEALTH DEPARTMENT DEFENDS SCOOTERS! “A vehicle matching the description was spotted in
Wilderness and police vehicles gave chase. “The suspected vehicle was successfully intercepted before
the driver jumped out from the moving vehicle which caused it to leave the road
and plunge into a gorge with a passenger inside who sustained minor injuries,”
Nkwalase said. Nkawalase said the suspect was taken to hospital for medical
treatment. “The suspect is expected to appear in the George Magistrate
Court on Monday to face charges of dealing in cannabis as well as reckless and
negligent driving,” he added.